.TH "scsi_test_unit_ready" 9 "scsi_test_unit_ready" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_test_unit_ready \- test if unit is ready
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_test_unit_ready
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "int timeout "  ","
.BI "int retries "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_sense_hdr *sshdr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
scsi device to change the state of.
.IP "timeout" 12
command timeout
.IP "retries" 12
number of retries before failing
.IP "sshdr" 12
outpout pointer for decoded sense information.

Returns zero if unsuccessful or an error if TUR failed.  For
removable media, UNIT_ATTENTION sets ->changed flag.
